Amira El Fadil (amụrụ na 15 Jenụwarị 1967) bụ onye ọrụ gọọmentị Sudan.

Ọ nọbu n'ọkwa Minista nke Social Welfare na Social Insurance maka Gọọmentị Sudan. N'afọ 2016, a họpụtara ya ka ọ rụọ ọrụ afọ anọ dị ka Kọmishọna na-ahụ maka mmekọrịta ọha na eze nke African Union Commission. Ọ bụkwa onye otu ndị isi nke World Anti-Doping Agency.
El Fadil arụwo ọrụ na Association of Women for Rural Development and Immigration, Women, Children and Family
O sonyere na Women's Rally for Peace ma duzie ọmụmụ ihe gbasara iwu udo na ngwọta esemokwu.
